    "desc": "Handcrafted design. Time-honored techniques. Genuine artisan skill. Investing in the empowerment and education of women and youth.",
    "navbar": "",
    "text": "Free shipping on orders of $100 or more in the US!\n0\nFALL IS HERE!\nCreate your ideal fall decor with our handmade pieces from Rwanda and Ghana!\nShop Now!\nBEST SELLING PRODUCTS\nWoven Trinket Basket\n$36.00 USD\nMini Plateau Neon\n$25.00 USD\nMini Pink Diamond Plateau\n$25.00 USD\nMini Pink Geo Plateau\n$25.00 USD\n‹\n›\nNOT YOUR AVERAGE NON-PROFIT.\nWhat began as a model to empower artisan women in post-genocide Rwanda has grown into an unwavering commitment to help artisans, unemployed youth and refugees across Africa participate in the artisan economy.\nThis is Indego Africa.\nWHAT OUR ARTISAN PARTNERS ARE SAYING\nEducation means so much to me. It is the most important legacy we can leave our descendants & the most powerful tool we can use to change people's lives.\nMarie Rose\nAkeza Cooperative\nOne thing I've learned is that we can achieve so much more together than we ever can alone.\nEsperance\nAkeza Cooperative\nI’ve learned to think big! My self-esteem has gone up and I am proud of the dignified and empowered woman I’ve become.\nJacqueline\nTwiyubake Cooperative\nFOLLOW US @INDEGO_AFRICA\nINDEGO AFRICA\nIndego Africa's market-driven approach to artisan empowerment helps transform the lives of women, youth, and refugees across Africa.\nMENU\nFinancials Get Involved FAQ Shop All Wholesale Shipping & Returns Stockists Contact Us\nNEWSLETTER\nLET'S BE FRIENDS\nFacebook Twitter Pinterest Instagram\n© All Rights Reserved 2022 . Indego Africa is a 501(c)(3) organization.",
